{"priority": "major", "kind": "proposal", "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{51a0cd5d-8697-4eb1-8b08-e919ee881e1c}ts=1694483"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "gazebo", "full_name": "osrf/gazebo", "uuid": "{51a0cd5d-8697-4eb1-8b08-e919ee881e1c}"}, "links": {"attachments": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/issues/1294/attachments_page=1.json"}, "self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/issues/1294.json"}, "watch": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/osrf/gazebo/issues/1294/watch"}, "comments": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/issues/1294/comments_page=1.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/issues/1294/inclusion-of-magnetic-field-strength"}, "vote": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/osrf/gazebo/issues/1294/vote"}}, "reporter": {"display_name": "Andrew Symington", "uuid": "{db1311fc-02e6-442e-84a1-4bb85dfee5ba}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bdb1311fc-02e6-442e-84a1-4bb85dfee5ba%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bdb1311fc-02e6-442e-84a1-4bb85dfee5ba%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:cab3b56e-7c24-487c-b07f-05e0600adf54/8a009f21-29b8-4d43-98ed-2677428e17ff/128"}}, "nickname": "asymingt", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:cab3b56e-7c24-487c-b07f-05e0600adf54"}, "title": "Inclusion of magnetic field strength sensor", "component": {"name": "sensors", "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/components/122877.json"}}}, "votes": 0, "watches": 5, "content": {"raw": "What would be really useful to multirotor research is the inclusion of a magnetic field strength sensor to compliment the IMU sensor already in Gazebo. What I propose is the following...\r\n\r\nIn the world SDF file...\r\n\r\n```\r\n#!xml\r\n\r\n<physics>\r\n   <magnetic>0.10 0.7 0.1</magnetic>\r\n</physics>\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd, in the model SDF file...\r\n\r\n```\r\n#!xml\r\n\r\n<sensor name=\"HMC5843\" type=\"magnetometer\">\r\n  <pose>0.01 0 0.03 0 -0 0</pose>\r\n  <magnetometer>\r\n    <noise>\r\n      <type>gaussian</type>\r\n      <mean>0.0</mean>\r\n      <stddev>0.01</stddev>\r\n    </noise>\r\n  </magnetometer>\r\n</sensor>\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe sensor itself would just take the global magnetic field strength vector, and rotate it from the world frame into the current sensor pose.\r\n\r\nThoughts?\r\n\r\n", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>What would be really useful to multirotor research is the inclusion of a magnetic field strength sensor to compliment the IMU sensor already in Gazebo. What I propose is the following...</p>\n<p>In the world SDF file...</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite language-xml\"><pre><span></span><span class=\"nt\">&lt;physics&gt;</span>\n   <span class=\"nt\">&lt;magnetic&gt;</span>0.10 0.7 0.1<span class=\"nt\">&lt;/magnetic&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"nt\">&lt;/physics&gt;</span>\n</pre></div>\n\n\n<p>And, in the model SDF file...</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite language-xml\"><pre><span></span><span class=\"nt\">&lt;sensor</span> <span class=\"na\">name=</span><span class=\"s\">&quot;HMC5843&quot;</span> <span class=\"na\">type=</span><span class=\"s\">&quot;magnetometer&quot;</span><span class=\"nt\">&gt;</span>\n  <span class=\"nt\">&lt;pose&gt;</span>0.01 0 0.03 0 -0 0<span class=\"nt\">&lt;/pose&gt;</span>\n  <span class=\"nt\">&lt;magnetometer&gt;</span>\n    <span class=\"nt\">&lt;noise&gt;</span>\n      <span class=\"nt\">&lt;type&gt;</span>gaussian<span class=\"nt\">&lt;/type&gt;</span>\n      <span class=\"nt\">&lt;mean&gt;</span>0.0<span class=\"nt\">&lt;/mean&gt;</span>\n      <span class=\"nt\">&lt;stddev&gt;</span>0.01<span class=\"nt\">&lt;/stddev&gt;</span>\n    <span class=\"nt\">&lt;/noise&gt;</span>\n  <span class=\"nt\">&lt;/magnetometer&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"nt\">&lt;/sensor&gt;</span>\n</pre></div>\n\n\n<p>The sensor itself would just take the global magnetic field strength vector, and rotate it from the world frame into the current sensor pose.</p>\n<p>Thoughts?</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "assignee": {"display_name": "Steve Peters", "uuid": "{2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/1fb4816dad9e68337d3096f750951f6cd=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsSP-1.png"}}, "nickname": "Steven Peters", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:5de38267-b118-494c-aa76-4fab35448816"}, "state": "new", "version": {"name": "3.0", "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/versions/100247.json"}}}, "edited_on": null, "created_on": "2014-10-09T11:19:27.502394+00:00", "milestone": null, "updated_on": "2016-06-08T01:02:12.451217+00:00", "type": "issue", "id": 1294}